title: For Trade:  Antique electric repulsion/induction motor looking for Saturday night special
postcontent:
I have this really neat 100+ year old electric motor that works. This is before electric motors had capacitors so it starts with brushes engaged and sparks flying, then centrifugal force pushes brushes out and induction takes over. These were made to last forever. Easy to "rebuild" as all they ever need it light sanding on commutator.  Here are some links to videos of it working. Would be great to use for saw or other old vintage shop tools.

Looking to sell my never used NIB Sage EBR chassis. Very cool chassis system for your M1A. Was going to build a Sage EBR clone and have decided to go a different route.

If you are not familiar with it this is a very popular chassis and scope mount as it is what the military has been using to re-purpose their M14's. The chassis increases accuracy and doesn't require a gunsmith to fiberglass or bed the action. Allows easy scope mounting and accessory mounting that you normally cant get with basic M1A stocks. and the adjustable comb cheek rest is very nice when running optics on a M1A. For additional info check out Sage's website:

http://www.sageinternationalltd.com/SIL/ebr.html

Picture doesn't do it justice. The FDE colored chassis is very hard to find and can be up to 6 months backorder.

will sell the Chassis w/o quick detach scope mount for $825.

Willing to trade for:
Glock 43 +cash
CZ 75 (SAO, SP01, Shadow, will add cash on my end if its a high end CZCustom shop model)

title: For Sale:  Ruger New Model Super Blackhawk 5.5" with available extras
postcontent:
I have a Ruger New Model Super Blackhawk with 5.5" barrel.  This revolver is in excellent condition and has not been shot much.  It has several minor marks in the blueing, but nothing major.  I purchased it from an older gentleman who hadn't fired it in 20 years and never shot it much.  I don't think I have put 100 rounds through it.  It has been reliable and accurate though and I have been regularly able to ring the gong target at 100 yards with all of my loads, even with cheap HSM cowboy loads.  If you know anything about these guns you know they are well known for being ultra tough and reliable.  I purchased this gun to use for grizzly bear defense when I moved to Montana and now that I have moved I have no real use for it so I am selling to try out some new hobbies.

The gun can also come with any combination of accessories as well as the original box and hard case as well as manual and even the lock and plastic wrap it came in.  I also have a basic hunter holster for it, a nice cowboy action style western holster and belt and a really comfortable chest holster (perfect for wearing with a backpack).  I have 2 6 round speed strips, 23 300 gr hunting or bear defense loads, and 88 plinking rounds.  In addition I have 44 mag dies and at least 300 pieces of starline brass as well as 250 or so Berry's bullets, 475 Missouri Cast Bullets, and 20 or so Cast Precision bullets that you can make an offer on.

I am asking 450 for the gun, 50 for the Triple K Cartridge Belt and Holster, 75 for the Chest Holster and 15 for the Hunter Holster.  I will sell the gun and all holsters for 550 and include the loaded ammo for another 25.  Make a fair offer for the reloading components, but I won't sell it until I sell the gun.

All laws apply!!!

The rifle will make a good coyote (if you're in Ohio) or deer (if you live somewhere else) rifle. It isn't so pretty that you'll feel bad if you scratch it up a little, but it's wood stock still looks good.  

The rifling in the barrel is still crisp (I have a photo of that, too).  It groups nicely.  

If you're interested in a good rifle that is going to deliver when you pull the trigger, let me know.  I am open to some discussion on price, but major lowballing isn't appreciated.  

I am willing to drive to meet other buyers who reside in Ohio and who are not prohibited from owning a firearm for any other reason.  If you are prohibited from owning a firearm, please do not contact me.
